Thank you again for anchoring the OB/GYN education booth and the prenatal counseling station yesterday. The Korean-language handouts on gestational diabetes moved faster than any other item at the booth; we ran out by 2 PM. The counseling station was quieter, four one-on-ones total but two of them turned into follow-up appointments at Brigham for next month, which is more than we had expected.

Would you write up a short booth-and-counseling recap for the Q1 Community Board packet? Keep it to what the day actually was - visits, handouts moved, follow-ups scheduled, any structural feedback for next year's fair setup. The board meets Friday November 20 at 6 PM; a two-paragraph note is fine, they read a lot of these and short is respected.

Please keep the recap in community-center voice, not clinical voice. The board members are volunteers from the Korean immigrant community; they read the reports for the human picture, not the technical picture. Individual patient details or clinical specifics do not belong in the recap - the same way we handled last year's fair write-up.

Also, please do not surface Umma's health situation in the recap or anywhere community-center-facing. I remember you were concerned last year that the community assumes you took on the fair booth because of her arthritis; that framing is not what we want on the board record.

Thank you for holding the day.

